title: Cullen Wilkerson
text:
Cullen Wilkerson (born September 7, 2004), is an American <a href="Association%20football">soccer</a> player who plays as a <a href="Midfielder%20%28association%20football%29">midfielder</a> for <a href="Portland%20Timbers%202">Portland Timbers 2</a> via the <a href="Portland%20Timbers">Portland Timbers</a> academy.
Club career.
After playing with the <a href="Portland%20Timbers">Portland Timbers</a> academy from 2019, Wilkerson appeared for Portland's <a href="USL%20Championship">USL Championship</a> side <a href="Portland%20Timbers%202">Portland Timbers 2</a> on August 3, 2020 as an 82nd-minute substitute in a 4–0 loss to rivals <a href="Tacoma%20Defiance">Tacoma Defiance</a>.
